63776.title: Various Fires No. 1
63776.credit_line: Purchased with funds provided by Mark Demerly and David Chalfie
rights: © New Catalogue (Luke Batten and Jonathan Sadler)

extended_text.content: Various Fires No. 1, among the first photos produced in the New Catalogue stock photography project, was created during a cross-country road trip when the artists agreed to stop and shoot a photograph every time they saw a fire of any variety. This photograph was taken in Kansas, where they came upon a family burning a termite-infested home on their property so that a newly married couple could rebuild there. The title of this work refers to the artist Edward Ruscha's 1964 photobook, Various Fires and Milk. New Catalogue claims to be influenced by Ruscha's non-narrative book format, about which he stated, "photography is dead as a fine art; its only place is in the commercial world."
extended_text.title: Gallery Label
